WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.099
Amen, and we have such a good God.

00:00:02.099 --> 00:00:03.799
He has been so good to us.

00:00:03.799 --> 00:00:07.440
And I told the teenagers this morning as we ended our class

00:00:07.440 --> 00:00:09.199
that I got a little statement on my desk

00:00:09.199 --> 00:00:10.500
that we thank God,

00:00:10.500 --> 00:00:12.560
not because our circumstances are always good,

00:00:12.560 --> 00:00:14.819
but because he is always good.

00:00:14.819 --> 00:00:18.200
And I'm so thankful for the many blessings

00:00:18.200 --> 00:00:19.799
in which he has bestowed upon me.

00:00:19.799 --> 00:00:22.879
Of course, this week, and we are mindful

00:00:22.879 --> 00:00:25.559
in the month of November here in America,

00:00:25.559 --> 00:00:27.520
we celebrate Thanksgiving.

00:00:27.520 --> 00:00:30.079
And it's always the fourth Thursday

00:00:30.079 --> 00:00:32.080
of the month of November.

00:00:32.080 --> 00:00:33.840
But I want you to be mindful of the fact

00:00:33.840 --> 00:00:37.240
that long before our nation officially proclaimed

00:00:37.240 --> 00:00:41.860
the holiday to celebrate God and his blessings

00:00:41.860 --> 00:00:43.119
and so on and so forth,

00:00:43.119 --> 00:00:46.159
we find that God instructed his people.

00:00:46.159 --> 00:00:48.759
And God has, as you study the Bible,

00:00:48.759 --> 00:00:51.520
given us instruction that we are to be thankful people.

00:00:51.520 --> 00:00:53.159
We're to praise and to give thanks

00:00:53.159 --> 00:00:55.880
and enters into his gates with thanksgiving.

00:00:55.919 --> 00:00:58.680
And we understand there's many portions of scripture

00:00:58.680 --> 00:01:01.279
that we can go to and we can read

00:01:01.279 --> 00:01:03.400
that God has given us that instruction.

00:01:03.400 --> 00:01:07.680
In fact, we find that consistently God is pleased

00:01:07.680 --> 00:01:11.160
when his people give thanks and when they rejoice.

00:01:11.160 --> 00:01:13.839
And we also find that as you study the word of God,

00:01:13.839 --> 00:01:15.879
that you'll find that God is not pleased

00:01:15.879 --> 00:01:17.519
when his people complain.

00:01:17.519 --> 00:01:19.620
In fact, we finished our lesson this morning

00:01:19.620 --> 00:01:22.639
with that truth from Numbers 11 in verse number one,

00:01:22.639 --> 00:01:25.800
that the people complained and it displeased the Lord

00:01:26.720 --> 00:01:29.120
and the Lord heard it and his anger was kindled

00:01:29.120 --> 00:01:32.720
against them and God is not pleased when we complain.

00:01:32.720 --> 00:01:36.379
But we did discover with the small group of us this morning

00:01:36.379 --> 00:01:39.680
that all of us acknowledge that it's easier to complain

00:01:39.680 --> 00:01:40.819
than it is to give thanks.

00:01:40.819 --> 00:01:44.519
It's more natural to complain.

00:01:44.519 --> 00:01:47.400
And part of that is our sin nature.

00:01:47.400 --> 00:01:48.900
But also I think that there's times

00:01:48.900 --> 00:01:51.400
in which we just take things for granted.

00:01:51.400 --> 00:01:54.739
And I mentioned to them this morning and I'm repeating it

00:01:54.739 --> 00:01:58.019
because I think it's worth us also considering this.

00:01:58.019 --> 00:02:01.260
I think probably most of us this morning at some point

00:02:01.260 --> 00:02:05.540
along our process of getting ready, flipped a light switch.

00:02:05.540 --> 00:02:07.019
And we flipped that light switch

00:02:07.019 --> 00:02:09.339
and we expected something to happen

00:02:09.339 --> 00:02:10.699
when we flipped the light switch

00:02:10.699 --> 00:02:14.699
and that was that the lights would turn on, right?

00:02:14.699 --> 00:02:16.619
How many of you thank God for that this morning

00:02:16.619 --> 00:02:18.080
when it happened?

00:02:18.080 --> 00:02:19.380
Probably not any of us.

00:02:19.380 --> 00:02:20.699
We just sometimes don't think about it,

00:02:20.699 --> 00:02:22.160
we take it for granted.

00:02:22.160 --> 00:02:24.059
I then said, how many of you brushed your teeth this morning

00:02:24.059 --> 00:02:25.479
and I hope all of you did.

00:02:26.699 --> 00:02:30.179
And you turned the faucet on and the water came out.

00:02:31.419 --> 00:02:32.580
Have you ever been in a place

00:02:32.580 --> 00:02:34.539
where the water didn't come out?

00:02:34.539 --> 00:02:37.020
And you said, oh man, this is a problem, right?

00:02:37.020 --> 00:02:39.259
But day after day and week after week,

00:02:39.259 --> 00:02:41.100
we take things for granted.

00:02:41.100 --> 00:02:43.539
And it gets us into a place where we're not mindful

00:02:43.539 --> 00:02:46.779
about giving thanks and being a thankful person.

00:02:46.779 --> 00:02:50.199
And we really have to be diligent and disciplined

00:02:50.199 --> 00:02:52.419
in our walk with the Lord that we would be,

00:02:52.419 --> 00:02:55.820
we would purpose to be someone who gives thanks.

00:02:55.820 --> 00:02:57.940
Many times in the book of Psalms you'll find

00:02:57.940 --> 00:02:58.779
that the Psalmist says,

00:02:58.779 --> 00:03:01.139
I will bless the Lord at all times.

00:03:01.139 --> 00:03:03.820
His praise shall continually be in my mouth.

00:03:03.820 --> 00:03:05.660
Psalm 34 and verse number one.

00:03:05.660 --> 00:03:07.660
But we see that I will statement,

00:03:07.660 --> 00:03:10.100
that purpose, that resolve,

00:03:10.100 --> 00:03:11.699
that I'm going to be an individual,

00:03:11.699 --> 00:03:15.220
I'm gonna be a child of God that praises my God.

00:03:15.220 --> 00:03:16.059
Why?

00:03:16.059 --> 00:03:18.119
Because there is much to be thankful for.

00:03:18.119 --> 00:03:20.979
We sang this morning that familiar Psalm

00:03:20.979 --> 00:03:23.779
or hymn, excuse me, count your blessings,

00:03:23.779 --> 00:03:25.539
name them one by one.

00:03:25.539 --> 00:03:27.300
We find that as we go through

00:03:27.300 --> 00:03:30.940
and we understand how the songwriter implores those

00:03:30.940 --> 00:03:33.460
that are hearing or even singing that song

00:03:33.460 --> 00:03:36.139
to name them one by one, to be reflective,

00:03:36.139 --> 00:03:39.979
to be purposed and to be thankful.

00:03:39.979 --> 00:03:41.300
And God is so good to us.

00:03:41.300 --> 00:03:44.059
I quoted already Psalm 68, 19,

00:03:44.059 --> 00:03:47.020
where the Bible says there in that portion of scripture,

00:03:47.020 --> 00:03:49.339
the rejoicing, blessed be the Lord

00:03:49.339 --> 00:03:51.899
who daily loadeth us with benefits,

00:03:51.899 --> 00:03:56.339
even the God of our salvation, Selah.

00:03:56.339 --> 00:03:57.660
And certainly this morning,

00:03:57.660 --> 00:03:58.979
I think that we would agree

00:03:58.979 --> 00:04:02.020
that God has daily loaded us with benefits.

00:04:02.020 --> 00:04:04.880
He's been so very good to us.

00:04:04.880 --> 00:04:07.100
This morning, as we look at Psalm 23,

00:04:07.100 --> 00:04:09.059
I'm gonna really just look at verse number four,

00:04:09.059 --> 00:04:10.699
I'll read the entire Psalm.

00:04:10.699 --> 00:04:12.779
But this morning, I wanna remind you

00:04:12.779 --> 00:04:16.380
and remind us of God's presence.

00:04:16.380 --> 00:04:19.420
I'm so thankful for this biblical truth

00:04:19.420 --> 00:04:21.260
that we find here in the book of Psalms,

00:04:21.260 --> 00:04:23.619
we find it in other portions of scripture as well.

00:04:23.619 --> 00:04:27.079
And Psalm 23 is a familiar passage of scripture,

00:04:27.079 --> 00:04:30.799
a passage that is often recited and rehearsed.

00:04:30.799 --> 00:04:33.619
And it's a precious portion of God's word.

00:04:33.619 --> 00:04:35.859
And notice the Bible begins in verse number one,

00:04:35.859 --> 00:04:40.859
the Lord is my shepherd, I shall not want.

00:04:41.100 --> 00:04:44.459
He maketh me to lie down in green pastures.

00:04:44.459 --> 00:04:47.739
He leadeth me beside the still waters.

00:04:47.739 --> 00:04:50.019
He restoreth my soul.

00:04:50.019 --> 00:04:53.140
He leadeth me in the paths of righteousness

00:04:53.140 --> 00:04:54.920
for his namesake.

00:04:54.920 --> 00:04:57.540
Yea, though I walk through the valley

00:04:57.540 --> 00:05:02.380
of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil

00:05:02.380 --> 00:05:06.320
for thou art with me.

00:05:06.320 --> 00:05:10.239
Thy rod and thy staff, they comfort me.

00:05:10.239 --> 00:05:12.339
Thou preparest a table before me

00:05:12.339 --> 00:05:14.739
in the presence of mine enemies.

00:05:14.739 --> 00:05:18.299
Thou anointest my head with oil.

00:05:18.299 --> 00:05:20.700
My cup runneth over.

00:05:20.700 --> 00:05:23.459
Surely, goodness and mercy shall follow me

00:05:23.459 --> 00:05:26.140
all the days of my life.

00:05:26.140 --> 00:05:30.579
And I will dwell in the house of the Lord forever.

00:05:31.480 --> 00:05:33.940
Again, a familiar portion of scripture,

00:05:33.940 --> 00:05:35.660
one in which I've preached from.

00:05:35.660 --> 00:05:38.420
There's been times that I've preached from Psalm 23

00:05:38.420 --> 00:05:40.859
as an entire message, getting through all six verses.

00:05:40.859 --> 00:05:42.820
There's been times that I've done a series

00:05:42.820 --> 00:05:45.799
through Psalm 23, and we've looked at it verse by verse.

00:05:45.799 --> 00:05:48.579
And the reality is that it's a passage of scripture

00:05:48.579 --> 00:05:50.700
that's packed with so much truth

00:05:50.700 --> 00:05:54.100
that really helps us to understand the relationship

00:05:54.100 --> 00:05:56.179
between us and our shepherd.

00:05:56.179 --> 00:05:58.700
I've often said, as I come to Psalm 23,

00:05:58.700 --> 00:06:00.500
that the Lord is the shepherd.

00:06:00.500 --> 00:06:02.619
He is the good shepherd, the great shepherd,

00:06:02.619 --> 00:06:04.059
the chief shepherd.

00:06:04.059 --> 00:06:05.179
If you look in the New Testament,

00:06:05.179 --> 00:06:08.019
you find all of those titles that would be ascribed

00:06:08.019 --> 00:06:09.380
to the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:06:09.380 --> 00:06:13.100
But here, the psalmist says, the Lord is my shepherd.

00:06:13.100 --> 00:06:15.899
And the reality is that he is the good shepherd,

00:06:15.899 --> 00:06:18.899
and as the good shepherd, he giveth his life for the sheep.

00:06:18.899 --> 00:06:21.380
He is the chief shepherd, and he's gonna appear.

00:06:21.380 --> 00:06:22.660
He is the great shepherd.

00:06:22.660 --> 00:06:26.619
And we understand those wonderful truths and realities,

00:06:26.619 --> 00:06:29.839
but we must recognize this morning the importance

00:06:29.839 --> 00:06:33.220
of ensuring that the good shepherd is my shepherd,

00:06:33.220 --> 00:06:35.299
that we have that personal relationship

00:06:35.299 --> 00:06:36.980
with the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:06:36.980 --> 00:06:39.299
We sang that song, Thank You, Lord,

00:06:40.119 --> 00:06:41.579
and talk about being thankful for salvation,

00:06:41.579 --> 00:06:43.279
which is rich and free.

00:06:43.279 --> 00:06:45.420
I'm so thankful that the Lord Jesus Christ,

00:06:45.420 --> 00:06:48.540
listen, it wasn't free for him, it was free for us.

00:06:48.540 --> 00:06:51.839
The gift requires someone to pay the price.

00:06:51.839 --> 00:06:54.179
I've often said to people out soul winning

00:06:54.179 --> 00:06:57.540
and knocking doors and engaging people in conversation,

00:06:57.540 --> 00:07:00.519
that the Bible says that the wage of sin is death,

00:07:00.519 --> 00:07:02.299
but the gift of God is eternal life

00:07:02.299 --> 00:07:04.019
through Jesus Christ, our Lord.

00:07:04.019 --> 00:07:08.239
And a gift is something that you have to either receive

00:07:08.239 --> 00:07:09.359
or you're gonna reject,

00:07:09.359 --> 00:07:13.720
but the gift had to be paid for by someone.

00:07:13.720 --> 00:07:17.279
The Lord Jesus Christ paid for the gift of eternal life

00:07:17.279 --> 00:07:18.920
with his precious blood.

00:07:18.920 --> 00:07:20.880
We're not redeemed with corruptible things,

00:07:20.880 --> 00:07:22.160
as Peter would say,

00:07:22.160 --> 00:07:24.559
but we're redeemed with the precious blood of Christ.

00:07:24.559 --> 00:07:27.160
And this morning, before I even get into the message

00:07:27.160 --> 00:07:29.679
and all the entirety of what we'll look at this morning,

00:07:29.679 --> 00:07:31.279
if you're here this morning and you say,

00:07:31.279 --> 00:07:33.160
I don't know that the Lord is my shepherd,

00:07:33.160 --> 00:07:35.600
I can't say, as the psalmist says here,

00:07:35.600 --> 00:07:38.760
the Lord is my shepherd.

00:07:38.760 --> 00:07:40.760
Remember this in John chapter number 10,

00:07:40.760 --> 00:07:45.399
the Lord Jesus Christ says, my sheep hear my voice,

00:07:45.399 --> 00:07:48.239
and they follow me and I give unto them eternal life

00:07:48.239 --> 00:07:50.279
and they shall never perish.

00:07:50.279 --> 00:07:55.279
And I'm so thankful this morning that here 27, 28 years ago,

00:07:56.320 --> 00:07:58.079
my life was changed forever

00:07:58.079 --> 00:08:00.959
because the shepherd became my shepherd.

00:08:00.959 --> 00:08:03.200
And I understood on that day that I was in need

00:08:03.239 --> 00:08:05.880
of the only savior, the Lord Jesus Christ,

00:08:05.880 --> 00:08:09.040
and you too this morning, if you're not sure of heaven today

00:08:09.040 --> 00:08:10.799
can be the day of your salvation.

00:08:10.799 --> 00:08:13.040
But let me draw for you this morning,

00:08:13.040 --> 00:08:15.239
for those of us that are saved this morning,

00:08:15.239 --> 00:08:17.559
if you look in verse number four,

00:08:17.559 --> 00:08:19.399
yea, though I walk through the valley

00:08:19.399 --> 00:08:22.399
of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil.

00:08:22.399 --> 00:08:24.239
And then the next phrase is the phrase

00:08:24.239 --> 00:08:27.399
in which I wanna focus on our attention this morning,

00:08:27.399 --> 00:08:32.159
for thou art with me, thy rod and thy staff,

00:08:32.159 --> 00:08:33.479
they comfort me.

00:08:33.479 --> 00:08:34.679
For a few minutes this morning,

00:08:34.679 --> 00:08:38.919
I wanna just simply meditate and muse upon that thought,

00:08:38.919 --> 00:08:43.919
that truth, that reality, thou art with me.

00:08:44.119 --> 00:08:46.840
Isn't it a precious truth of God's word?

00:08:46.840 --> 00:08:49.159
We'll get to it eventually at the end of the message,

00:08:49.159 --> 00:08:52.159
but over there in Hebrews,

00:08:52.159 --> 00:08:53.320
the Bible talks about the fact

00:08:53.320 --> 00:08:56.440
that I will never leave thee nor forsake thee.

00:08:56.440 --> 00:08:59.559
In fact, oftentimes as we speak about promises

00:08:59.559 --> 00:09:01.960
that God has given to us in his word,

00:09:02.719 --> 00:09:06.039
we'll ask people for, hey, standing on the promises,

00:09:06.039 --> 00:09:09.880
share some promises, and it seems as if that one

00:09:09.880 --> 00:09:14.320
is one that is regularly mentioned that God is with us.

00:09:14.320 --> 00:09:16.919
This morning as we really ponder the thought

00:09:16.919 --> 00:09:18.880
and consider this morning that there's no place

00:09:18.880 --> 00:09:21.799
that I can go away from the presence of God,

00:09:21.799 --> 00:09:25.000
and one day I will be in his presence in heaven,

00:09:25.000 --> 00:09:28.239
I'll see him face to face, and I look forward to that day.

00:09:28.239 --> 00:09:31.400
But the reality is that he's promised to be with us today.

00:09:32.479 --> 00:09:34.039
Thou art with me.

00:09:34.039 --> 00:09:35.799
And I want you to think about God's presence

00:09:35.799 --> 00:09:37.640
if you're taking notes this morning.

00:09:37.640 --> 00:09:41.520
Number one, God's presence brings comfort.

00:09:41.520 --> 00:09:44.479
God's presence brings comfort.

00:09:44.479 --> 00:09:45.599
You know, we live in a world

00:09:45.599 --> 00:09:48.159
in which there's so many things going on.

00:09:48.159 --> 00:09:51.479
There's so many trials and difficulties

00:09:51.479 --> 00:09:54.320
and things that can bring anxiety and worry

00:09:54.320 --> 00:09:58.400
into the lives of people, including the people of God.

00:09:58.400 --> 00:10:00.280
Listen, if worry didn't affect you,

00:10:00.280 --> 00:10:03.700
then God wouldn't have to say be careful for nothing.

00:10:03.700 --> 00:10:05.880
But because it does impact us,

00:10:05.880 --> 00:10:07.240
and we do live in this world,

00:10:07.240 --> 00:10:08.760
though we're not of this world,

00:10:08.760 --> 00:10:12.200
we face circumstances, we face difficulties and trials

00:10:12.200 --> 00:10:14.280
and what have you, and there are times

00:10:14.280 --> 00:10:18.640
in which we have that time of maybe anxiety and worry

00:10:18.640 --> 00:10:21.080
and we're fretting and so on and so forth,

00:10:21.080 --> 00:10:24.120
but we find that God's presence brings comfort.

00:10:24.120 --> 00:10:26.320
Can I encourage you this morning to understand

00:10:26.320 --> 00:10:29.560
